The description below is common to all 90-198 Pt isotope          7843 1451
evaluations.                                                      7843 1451
                                                                  7843 1451
Fast neutron evaluations for nine Pt isotopes were merged with    7843 1451
ENDF/B-VIII.0 resonance regions.                                  7843 1451
                                                                  7843 1451
The chain of isotopes has been evaluated in parallel in order to  7843 1451
make use of experimental data taken on the natural element,       7843 1451
which often are the most reliable source of information. In the   7843 1451
case ofPt the evaluation methodology was the same as the one      7843 1451
used for 181Ta. Dealing with a chain of several isotopes implies  7843 1451
that the consistency requirement must be imposed. We need to      7843 1451
ensure that the same model parameters are used when a given       7843 1451
isotope appears in different calculations. Technically, this      7843 1451
condition was imposed by defining the common input file           7843 1451
containing all input parameters except those pertinent to the     7843 1451
particular target , such as target A and Z, or coupled-channels   7843 1451
coupling scheme. This file was included while reading input       7843 1451
files for the individual isotopes. We used superfluid EGSM level  7843 1451
densities (except of 198Pt for which Gilbert-Cameron level        7843 1451
densities were used), and HRTW width fluctuation correction.      7843 1451
                                                                  7843 1451
The shape of the calculated capture cross sections is very        7843 1451
similar to the Koehler 2013 measurements.  We only scaled         7843 1451
down calculated cross sections with a single, energy-             7843 1451
independent factor per each isotope. These factors, which         7843 1451
multiply the original MLO1 gamma-strength, are closer to 1        7843 1451
than the default factors resulting from normalization to the      7843 1451
thermal gamma width.  Choosing to follow isotopic measurements    7843 1451
by Koehler we underestimate by about 5% the respectable           7843 1451
experiments on the natural platinum that were very                7843 1451
well reproduced with the default (thermal normalization)          7843 1451
calculations. There is a disagreement between these experiments   7843 1451
and those by Koehler. The LANSCE results will help to make a      7843 1451
final decision.                                                   7843 1451
                                                                  7843 1451
Elemental (n,2n) cross sections by Frehaut, corrected by a        7843 1451
factor of 1.078,  are  well reproduced by the new evaluation.     7843 1451
The  ENDF/B-VIII.0 is a bit lower but equally good. The two       7843 1451
evaluations differ mostly in the high energy tail where no        7843 1451
experimental data exist.                                          7843 1451
                                                                  7843 1451
In the case of (n,p) and (n,$\alpha$) reactions we followed       7843 1451
primarily data by Filatenkov. Ground-state cross sections agree   7843 1451
with ENDF/B-VIII.0 within uncertainties. No isomeric meta state   7843 1451
cross sections are given in the current ENDF/B-VIII.0             7843 1451
evaluations. Our (n,p) isomeric and ground state cross sections   7843 1451
reproduce measurements but at the price of modifying              7843 1451
particle-hole spin distribution in the preequilibrium emission    7843 1451
of protons.  The quite significant reduction is likely related    7843 1451
to the fact that Multistep Direct mechanism, that is here         7843 1451
simulated by the exciton model, favors low angular momentum       7843 1451
transfer populating states with the spin close to the ground      7843 1451
state.                                                            7843 1451
                                                                  7843 1451
The covariances were calculated used Kalman filter and include    7843 1451
cross-reaction correlations. Cross-isotope correlations were      7843 1451
not accounted for which implies that uncertainties are somewhat   7843 1451
overestimated since data on natural Pt were not considered in     7843 1451
uncertainty quantification.                                       7843 1451
